args:
While helping out in the slums, Ranzal learns
Gatov is not only giving charitably to the poor,
but is trying to change the entire systemâ€”
which leaves a strong impression on him.
But then Templars appear on the scene and
attempt to take the prince's party prisoner.
Buckle down, you sods! Watch your\nopponents' movements carefully!
Pretty noisy bunch ya got there, pal.\nWhat's the deal? Lookin' to maybe\ngo pick a fight or three somewhere?
Actually, this is a training center for new\nmembers of the Watch. ...Oy! He's here!
Hey, you're that traveler I've heard about.\nGatov says you're a skilled warrior.

I was wondering if you mind helping to
train these folks? They've got will to spare,
but being self-taught, the actual skill set
is rather lacking.
Appreciate it. All right, you sods!\nToday you're getting a special lesson!

All right, let's call it a day right there.
It ain't bad, but yer too damn fired up.
Ya gotta pay closer attention to yer
surroundings in a fight, yeah?
Looks like our boys really learned a thing\nor two today. Thanks again.
Happy to help. Frankly, I'm surprised ya\neven have a spot to be trainin' people\nhow to swing a sword in a place like this.
Oh, it's not only swordsâ€”we also have\nplaces to train people in smithing and\nvarious other artisan craftworks.
It took us a long time to get to this point,\nand it's only the beginning.
We don't want our work to stop here.\nWe want to expand this and set up\nfacilities in poor areas everywhere.

Eventually, we'd like to make a school for
children as well as a proper hospital.
Perhaps even an interest-free bank that
will loan capital to businesses.
Quite the big thinker, ain't ya?
Oh, I'm just the boots on the ground.\nThe actual ideas manâ€”and the one who\nputs everything in motionâ€”is Gatov.

No kiddin'. He's the one who put together
the Watch to begin withâ€”assembled it
from whatever rogues, bandits, and
cutpurses happened to wander into town.
Every single person being trained here\nhas at least one skeleton in the closest,\nif not a whole graveyard's worth.

But most folks only take up the criminal
life because they have no other choice.
If you give them food, shelter, and work
they can be proud of, they'll change.
Gatov believes that, and he isn't afraid of\nwho knows it. And the more he talked\nabout it, the bigger our group got.
I take it you ain't immune to the whole\nï¼‚shady pastï¼‚ deal too, yeah?
I lost my hometown and family in the war.\nI was hopeless when Gatov rescued me.\nDesperate, even.
If you wish people to truly escape poverty,\nyou can't simply hand them a loaf of bread\nand call it a day.
You need to settle in and concentrate on\nactually changing the systemâ€”or at least\nthat's what Gatov always says.
Who knows? But whatever his past or true\nidentity may be, the fact is that everyone\nhere relies on him.
He's a man who thinks for himself and\nworks hard, and everyone who follows him\nbelieves in him without reservation.
That mutual trust must make all this stuff\nyer tryin' to do a hell of a lot easier.
The Templars are marching on our district!
Those are the guys what tried to\nput the screws to us before!
It's incredibly rare for the Templar order to\nset foot in our district, and I don't like it\none bit. We need to hurry back.
Out of the way! Let us pass!
How about you just shut the hell up?\nYou got no jurisdiction here!
Your lot don't serve and protect nothin' but\nyourselves, and you're dreamin' if you\nthink we're gonna let you in!
By the order of Her Holiness the Pope,\nwe are taking this group into custody!
You got a warrant from the king for that,\nfriend? 'Cause no warrant means no entry!
Silence! If you live in this city, you know\nfull well it is the papacy that holds power,\nnot the monarchy.
Why have people from the Church\ncome all the way out here?!
They want Gatov's guests. We've held 'em\nat the entrance, but it's only a matter of \ntime before they break through.
Well, hell. That means they're after us.\nSorry to bring this kinda heat down on ya.
Think nothing of it; it's only natural that\nwe would protect our guests. For now,\nlet's head back to base.
There's a big fuss goin' on outside,\nand the way to the street is bein'\nblockaded by Grams Templars.
Okay, so let's just use Zena's power\nand zap ourselves outta here!
Unfortunately, there is a powerful magic\nbarrier around this entire city.
As such, I cannot use that spell.
Why the heck would they have\nsomething like that?!
It is likely the Pope's doing.

I hear that the Pope of the Ilian Church of
Grams is, in fact, an Auspex possessed of
a power great enough to open doors to
other worlds.
So she must be using some kind of sorcery\nto prevent us from escaping.
Well, if push comes to shove, you'll just\nhave to break through with our help.
If we did that, the Watch would suffer\nlosses of their own. We can't ask your\npeople to risk their lives for us.
The boss is rightâ€”we need another plan.\nDon't suppose there's some kinda secret\nway we could sneak outta here?
Actually, there IS a back alley that will\ntake you around to the main street.

Well, remaining here is not an option.
But if we can reach a place with lots of
peopleâ€”and find a little luck on the wayâ€”
we might be able make good our escape.
In that case, please show us\nhow to reach this back alley.
Follow me. I'll show you, then find Gatov\nand tell him what's going on.
Looks like the coast is clear...\nC'mon out, everyone!
Thanks, Luca. Now we'll just blend into\nthe crowds and make our wayâ€”
Did you even LOOK before you waved\nus all out here, you big dummy?!
You're going to be swabbing the decks\nas punishment when we get back.
It seems we will have to fight our way free\nof this situation after all. I must say,\nI'm rather looking forward to this.
Then let's do what we must\nto break free of this place!
